<div type="translation" source="bib:Gillet2024_01">

<p>Fortune! Prosperity! This is the 26th year of Kōpparakesarivarman who has taken Madurai. To Mahādeva of Tiruvalāntuṟai of Ciṟupaḻuvūr, a <foreign>brahmadeya</foreign> of Kuṉṟakkūṟṟam, lord <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>uṭaiyāṉ</foreign></supplied> of Iṭaiyāṟṟuppātticūrai, Aṭikaṇiḷavi, placed <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>vaitta</foreign></supplied> to burn <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>eriya</foreign></supplied> one <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>oṉṟu</foreign></supplied> perpetual lamp <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>nontāviḷakku</foreign></supplied>, placed <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>vaitta</foreign></supplied> 90 undying and non-ageing great goats <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>cāvāmūvāp perāṭu</foreign></supplied>. This is under the protection of the Panmāheśvaras.</p></div>

